The paper deals with mechanism design and pricing problems, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves private information about capacities, which suggests a connection to the field of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the concavity of the revenue function, which is a topic in mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The Bayesian setting and probability distributions suggest a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with pricing and revenue maximization, which are topics in the field of economics and market design (cs.EC).
